## Solution: Use `@@added` to version the spread property

When you spread `...ManagedServiceIdentityProperty`, it creates an `identity` property on your resource in **all** versions. To restrict it to `2025-05-04-preview` only, add an **augment decorator** after your model:

```typespec
model MyResource is TrackedResource<MyResourceProperties> {
  ...ResourceNameParameter<MyResource>;
  ...ManagedServiceIdentityProperty;   // keep the spread
}

// Version the resulting property
@@added(MyResource.identity, Versions.`2025-05-04-preview`);
```

### Key points

- Target the **concrete property** `MyResource.identity`, not the spread model itself.
- If your PATCH/update model also gained `identity`, version that member separately too.
- Validate with `tsp compile .` and confirm `identity` is absent in older version output and present in `2025-05-04-preview`.

**References:** [ARM versioning](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/arm/versioning) · [Evolving APIs](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/versioning/06-evolving-apis) · [ManagedServiceIdentityProperty](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/libraries/azure-resource-manager/reference/data-types)
